node.text:
In February of last year, we were honored to receive a message from @thehouseofmandela about working together on a project to spread awareness of the Mandela Freedom Project, Mandela Day, and to honor the legacy of Nelson Mandela. We had the fortune of working directly with Nelson Mandela’s daughter Makaziwe Mandela, his granddaughter Tukwini Mandela, and the House of Mandela to design a special capsule collection, as well as host volunteer and donation initiatives that align with the family’s values.

Mandela Day is a global call to action that celebrates the idea that each individual has the power to transform the world and the ability to make an impact. It is not meant to be a public holiday, but as a day to uphold the legacy of Nelson Mandela and his values through volunteering and community service. Mandela fought for social justice for 67 years, we’re asking you to start with 67 minutes.

We sat down with Nelson Mandela’s grandson @kwekumandela to discuss how his grandfather impacted him and his family’s life and purpose, his perspective on today’s current landscape, Mandela Day, and more.

This Monday we will launch a capsule with the House of Mandela where proceeds will be donated to different organizations that align with the Six Pillars of Mandela. These include #HashtagLunchBag, Black Girls CODE, and The Innocence Project.

node.text:
To celebrate the holiday, we’ve partnered with the Martin Luther King Jr. Estate and his son Martin Luther King III to pay tribute to Dr. King and continue to spread the message of his vision. 

Kith’s own @marlonbeck2 had a conversation with @officialmlking3 at Dr. King’s childhood home and church in Atlanta to talk about how the youth can continue the pursuit of change in America.

This Monday we will launch a capsule with the MLK Jr. Estate where 100% of the proceeds will be donated. 50% will go to @officialmlking3’s foundation, the Drum Major Institute. The other 50% will be evenly distributed to the Youth Direct Action Fund, March for Our Lives, Do Something, and the Alliance for Youth Action.

Directed by @rayneutron

Together with @bmw we have designed our own version of the newest generation of the M4 Competition, making significant modifications to the interior and exterior. This limited-edition model will be produced in 150 units worldwide across three color options that will be available to the public for pre-order starting today at 11AM EST.

The modifications begin with the interior. The M Carbon bucket seats have been redesigned in a tri-color makeup inspired by the M color palette. The black merino leather has also been embossed with the Kith Monogram pattern on the front and rear headrests and center armrest. 

On the exterior, the rear decklid features a black Kith logo in BMW’s Motorsport font with the iconic tri-color M stripes. Customers will also have the option to have the Kith Motorsport logo woven into the fibers of the carbon fiber roof for an additional charge.

Kith has also redesigned the roundel emblem on the hood, marking the first time in BMW’s history that a production car will feature an updated roundel. This emblem adds a circle around the BMW roundel in the iconic M color palette and says “KITH • ESTABLISHED 2011 • 2021 IN PARTNERSHIP WITH BMW • M4 COMPETITION”. These words establish Kith and BMW’s relationship, as well as nod to the fact that these cars will deliver to customers in 2021, which is Kith’s tenth anniversary as a brand.

Lastly, this model will be offered exclusively in three matte paint finishes: Frozen Black (shown in video), Frozen Dark Silver, and Frozen Brilliant White. 

These design elements are meant to further enhance the new M4 Competition, which will come with BMW M’s TwinPower Turbo 3.0 Liter inline-six cylinder engine to deliver 503 horsepower.

The BMW M4 Competition x Kith is limited strictly to 150 units worldwide and is available for pre-order TODAY at 11AM EST on the BMW website and Kith.com.

More info via link in bio.

node.text:
In February of last year, we were honored to receive a message from @thehouseofmandela about working together on a project to spread awareness of the Mandela Freedom Project, Mandela Day, and to honor the legacy of Nelson Mandela. We had the fortune of working directly with Nelson Mandela’s daughter Makaziwe Mandela, his granddaughter Tukwini Mandela, and the House of Mandela to design a special capsule collection, as well as host volunteer and donation initiatives that align with the family’s values.

Mandela Day is a global call to action that celebrates the idea that each individual has the power to transform the world and the ability to make an impact. It is not meant to be a public holiday, but as a day to uphold the legacy of Nelson Mandela and his values through volunteering and community service. Mandela fought for social justice for 67 years, we’re asking you to start with 67 minutes.

We sat down with Nelson Mandela’s grandson @kwekumandela to discuss how his grandfather impacted him and his family’s life and purpose, his perspective on today’s current landscape, Mandela Day, and more.

This Monday we will launch a capsule with the House of Mandela where proceeds will be donated to different organizations that align with the Six Pillars of Mandela. These include #HashtagLunchBag, Black Girls CODE, and The Innocence Project.

Devote your life. Master your craft.

As we celebrate our 10th anniversary with the release of the Fieg for New Balance RC1300, we reflect on the journey that brought us here. In doing so, we wanted to highlight others who devoted their lives to master their own crafts.

This campaign includes recording artist and entrepreneur Ryan Leslie, iconic chef and restaurateur Nobu Matsuhisa, multidisciplinary artist Daniel Arsham, jewelry designer Martine Ali, bespoke tailor Leonard Logsdail, ceramist Lucy Park, and chess aficionado Anthony Williams.

View the full campaign and learn more about each of these masters of craft via link in bio.

The Fieg for New Balance RC1300 10th Anniversary capsule releases this Monday, July 12, at Kith shops & 11AM EST on Kith.com.

We are proud to announce the official opening of Sadelle’s at Kith Paris. Operating at 100% capacity tomorrow, July 1st.

Together with Major Food Group, we have brought our favorite New York brunch restaurant to Paris, making it the first international Sadelle’s outpost.

Located on the first floor of the Kith Paris flagship, we will bring a taste of New York to our new Paris community.

For more info and continued updates, visit @sadellesatkithparis
-
Nous sommes fiers d'annoncer l'ouverture officielle du Sadelle's chez Kith Paris. Sadelle’s fonctionne maintenant à 100% de sa capacité.

En collaboration avec Major Food Group, nous avons installé notre restaurant de brunch new-yorkais préféré à Paris, ce qui en fait le premier établissement international de Sadelle.

Situé au rez-de-chaussée du flagship de Kith Paris, nous apportons le parfum de New York à notre nouvelle communauté parisienne.

Pour plus d’informations et suivre les dernières actualités, visitez @sadellesatkithparis
